            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab>(S) Dum in Dei nomine, in <rs key="#Comitatus">comitatu</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Comitatus" ref="#estates/83">Florentino</geogName>, prope
                            <rs key="#Rivers">fluvium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers">Arni</placeName>, in loco qui nominatur <placeName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Mention #Residential #Itinerary"
                            ref="#places/533">Omiclo</placeName> in iudicio residebat domnus
                            <persName key="#Chancellor #Missus_regis"><name ref="Guntherius"
                                >Gunterius</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancelarius</rs> et <rs key="#Missus_regis"
                            >missus</rs> domni inperatoris iusticias faciendas ac delibearandas,
                        adesent cum eo <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Bonusfilius"
                                >Bonusfilius</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Otto">Otto</name></persName>, <persName
                            key="#Judge #Missus_regis"><name ref="Atto">Atto</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Wibertus">Wiberto</name></persName>,
                            <persName key="#Judge"><name ref="Burgundius"
                            >Burgundius</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"><name
                                ref="Wolcausus">Wolcausus</name></persName>, <persName key="#Judge"
                                ><name ref="Tolbertus">Tolbertus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Judge">iudices</rs> sacri palacii et reliqui plures. Ibique eorum
                        veniens presencie <persName key="#Advocatus"><name ref="Lanfrancus"
                                >Lanfrancus</name></persName>, <rs key="#Advocatus">avocatus</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">monesterii</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/126">Sancti
                            Bartholomei</orgName>, sito loco qui vocatur <placeName
                            key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/281">Curtis Mainberti</placeName>, et
                        cepit dicere: “Iam plures vice me reclamavi ad vos, donnus Gunterius
                        cancelarius et missus, super <persName><name ref="Bonifacius"
                                >Bonefacium</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Ebbo"
                                >Eponem</name></persName> et supra <persName><name ref="Rainerius"
                                >Ranerium</name></persName> filium <persName><name ref="Willa"
                                >Wille</name></persName> qui parti predicti monesterii malo ordine
                        et contra legem detinent <foreign><rs key="#Landed_possessions">omne quod
                                abemus</rs> in <placeName key="#Landed_possessions"
                                ref="#places/348">Alma</placeName></foreign> et contradicent
                        nominative medietatem de <rs key="#Curtes">curte</rs> una que noncupatur
                            <geogName key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Churches"
                            ref="#estates/235"><placeName ref="#places/281" key="#Curtes #Churches"
                                >Sesstinga</placeName></geogName> cum <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casis</rs> et <rs key="#Churches"
                            >capellis</rs> seu teritoriis omnibusque rebus que ad ipsam medietatem
                        de iamdicta corte et capella pertinente; nam aliam medietatem de iamdicta
                        corte et capella sive rebus omnibus ad parte suprascripto monesterii a
                        proprietatem pertinet;. Et sive medietate de curte una qui noncupatur
                            <geogName key="#Curtes #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Churches"
                            ref="#estates/236"><placeName key="#Curtes" ref="#places/534"
                                >Columnata</placeName></geogName> cum ecclexiis casis teritoriis et
                        omnibus rebus que ad ipsa medietas de predicta curte et ecclesiis pertinet;
                        reliquam namque medietas pars ipsius monesterii a proprietatem ipsius
                        monesterii detinent. Unde quero ad vos, donnus cancellarius et missus, ut
                        vos propter Deum et anime domni imperatoris ac vestre mercedis, ut
                        investiatis me et parti predicti monesterii de is omnibus rebus ad salva
                        querela, quoqusque ipsi Bonefacius et Eppo et Rainerius ad vestrum placito
                        veninant, et ad predicti monesterii iustitiam faciant”. Cum ipse Lanfrancus
                        avocatus taliter retulisent, tunc domnus Gunterius cancelarius et missus per
                        fuste, quam sua tenebat manum, investivit predictum Lanfrancum avocatum et
                        predictum monesterium de suprascriptis medietatibus vel duabus curtibus,
                        siccuti supra denominantur ad salva querellam, quodusque predictus
                        Bonefacius et Eppo et Rainerius ad placitum veniant et predicti monesterii
                        iusticia faciant. Et insuper mixit <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium"
                            >bannum</rs> ex parte domni imperatoris, ut nullus quislibet eundem
                        Lanfrancum parte predicti monesterii de is omnibus rebus devestire molestare
                        vel inquietare audeat sine legale iudicio. Qui vero fecerit centum libras
                        auri se conpoxiturus agnoscad, medietatem <rs key="#Camera_regis"
                            >camere</rs> domni imperatoris, medietatem parti predicti monesterii. Et
                        ac noticia qualiter acta est causa fieri amonuerunt. Quidem et ego <persName
                            key="#Writer #Notary"><name ref="Aldus">Aldus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Notary">notarius</rs> sacri palaci et iusione suprascripto
                        cancelalarii et misso seu iudicum amonicione scripsi. Hanno ab incarnacione
                        domini nostris Iesu Christi milleximo quimquageximo quinto, imperii vero
                        domni secundi Einrigi Deo propicio nono, quartodecimo die mensis iunii,
                        indicione octava. Ego Guntherius cancellarius confirmavi (SR). (S)
                        Bonusfilius <rs key="#Judge">iudex</rs> sacri palatii interfuit. (S) Atzo
                        iudex et <rs key="#Missus_regis">missus</rs> domni imperatoris interfuit.
                        (S) Ego Otto iudex sacri palatii interfui. (S) Ego Wibertus iudex sacri
                        palacii interfui. (S) Ego Burgundius iudex sacri palatii interfui. (S)
                        Walcausus iudex sacri palatii interfuit.</ab>
